<TITLE> Hillary sends Bangla New Year greetings </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 13 (bdnews24.com)  US secretary of state Hillary Clinton has sent greetings for the Bangla New Year 1417, to be celebrated on April 14. "On behalf of President Barack Obama and the American people, I congratulate all Bengalis as you celebrate Pohela Boishakh and welcome a new year of promise and possibility," she said in a message issued by the US embassy in Dhaka on Tuesday. She noted that the occasion "unites people of common heritage across religious and national lines, and is an opportunity to honor Bengali culture with music, drama and traditional foods." Clinton also remembered the 150th birth anniversary of the great poet Rabindranath Tagore, which will be celebrated in 1417. Tagore's "writing has enriched our common humanity and brought pride to Bengali people around the world," she 
